      "content": "but that's just a nice way to look at it. in reality, once people see you like this, they don't see a \"new story,\" they just see the disaster. the shame is permanent. it's like, how do you even live with that weight? how do you even walk around knowing you're just a walking embodiment of everything that went wrong? it feels like the only way to actually stop the feeling, to stop the embarrassment, is to just... not be here to feel it anymore. it feels like the only way to preserve any dignity left is to just exit before the fallout gets even worse.",
